cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG 

This paper is about generating high-quality hair images using generative models, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The proposed method involves using a re-generating network with self-enhancing capability, which involves extracting texture and orientation maps from hair images, indicating that it could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper extensively evaluates its approach and compares it to state-of-the-art methods, indicating that it could also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
